posts.raw_content:
You’re never going to see a better administration in your lifetime. Some of you need to get a grip and manage expectations.

Trump isn’t a king. He can’t just do everything he wants to do. He can’t just build the wall. He can’t just “arrest all the criminals.” He cannot just end all immigration overnight.

He’s limited by corrupt courts, corrupt Congress, a corrupt media, and a retarded NPC public — about half of which are invaders and aren’t real Americans, but can vote because their worthless parents plopped out a baby on US soil.

That being said, with the options Trump has, has he done a good job? YES. He’s a done a spectacular job. He is doing every realistic thing that can be done. 

You guys freak out over trivial issues like Trump not reducing the number of Chinese students, reforming but not ending H1Bs completely, and supporting ISRAEL (REEEE every president ever has supported Israel —this doesn’t matter to anyone but terminally online zoomers who have a child’s understanding of foreign policy and Middle East history). Chinese students aren’t going to “spy” on us by gaining access to public universities and Econ 101 classes you can take online. 100k H1Bs per year isn’t going to “replace us.” It’s ok to disagree with these policies, I’d rather there be ZERO h1B visas, but stop making mountains out of molehills. 

All of us are dealing with the tragic death of western society and America. None of us want to be here. Whining and being low energy doesn’t help. 

In a world full of whiny Nick Fuentes faggots, be a Charlie Kirk. Focus on what you can control. Don’t criticize people on topics you don’t really understand. Don’t tell people like Kash and Bongino how to do their jobs when they’ve been doing their jobs longer than you’ve been alive.

Don’t ask what the Trump admin can do for you. Ask what you can do for the Trump admin. We can save America but it won’t happen from whining. It will happen if we all do our personal best to help stop the commies. Quit whining on every post and develop your career so you can do something useful in the future. We need more Charlies not more whiny cunts screaming about nonsense and killing the high energy we need to do anything.
